<p><strong>Languages</strong> any four languages</p>

<p><strong>Challenge</strong> 6 (2,300 XP)</p>

<p><strong><em>Spellcasting.</em></strong> The conjurer is a 9th-level spellcaster. Its spellcasting ability is intelligence (spell save DC 14, +6 to hit with spell attacks). The conjurer has the following wizard spells prepared:</p>

<p>Cantrips (at will): acid splash, mage hand, poison spray, prestidigitation</p>

<p>1st level (4 slots): mage armor, magic missile, unseen servant*</p>

<p>2nd level (3 slots): cloud of daggers<em>, misty step</em>, web*</p>

<p>3rd level (3 slots): fireball, stinking cloud*</p>

<p>4th level (3 slots): Evardâ€™s black tentacles*, stoneskin</p>

<p>5th level (2 slots): cloudkill<em>, conjure elemental</em></p>

<p>*Conjuration spell of 1st level or higher</p>

<p><strong><em>Benign Transportation (Recharges after the Conjurer Casts a Conjuration Spell of 1st Level or Higher).</em></strong> As a bonus action, the conjurer teleports up to 30 feet to an unoccupied space that it can see. If it instead chooses a space within range that is occupied by a willing Small or Medium creature, they both teleport, swapping places.</p>

<p><strong>Actions</strong></p>

<p><strong><em>Dagger.</em></strong> Melee or Ranged Weapon Attack: +5 to hit, reach 5 ft. or range 20/60 ft., one target. Hit: 4 (1d4+2) piercing damage.</p>

